# InventoryHub

InventoryHub is a full-stack inventory management application built with a Blazor front-end and a Minimal API back-end. The application retrieves product data from the API and displays product details including name, price, stock, and category.

This project demonstrates front-end and back-end integration, API debugging, CORS configuration, structured JSON responses, error handling, and performance optimization using memory caching.

Microsoft Copilot was used to help generate the integration code, debug API route and CORS issues, structure nested JSON responses, improve error handling, and suggest performance optimizations.
